    "What documents does a lender need for mortgage approval?",
    "Mortgage underwriting requires thorough documentation of your financial picture. Standard document package: **Income verification**: W-2 employees: 2 years of W-2s, 30 days of pay stubs, possibly last 2 years tax returns. Self-employed: 2 years personal tax returns (all schedules), 2 years business tax returns, year-to-date P&L, 12-24 months bank statements. Retirees: Social Security award letter, pension statements, IRA/401k statements. Rental income: Schedule E from tax returns, current leases. **Asset documentation**: 2-3 months of bank statements (all accounts, all pages). Investment/retirement account statements. Gift letter (if any gift funds for down payment). **Liability information**: Lender pulls credit report — lists all debts. Explanation letters for any derogatory items (late payments, collections). Divorce decree (if applicable). **Other as needed**: Bankruptcy discharge papers (if applicable). Explanation letters for employment gaps, large deposits, or other anomalies. VA Certificate of Eligibility (for VA loans). Disability income documentation. **During underwriting (be ready to respond fast)**: Underwriter conditions — lenders routinely request additional documentation during processing. A fast response is critical to staying on schedule. Missing a lender request by even 24-48 hours can jeopardize your closing date."
