    "What is USDA financing and who qualifies?",
    "USDA loans (Section 502 Guaranteed Loans) are government-backed mortgages for rural and suburban homebuyers — offering zero down payment for qualifying properties and borrowers. Key benefits: Zero down payment. No PMI (guarantee fee instead, typically lower than FHA MIP). Competitive interest rates. Can include closing costs in the loan (if appraised value supports it). Qualifications: Property must be in a USDA-eligible rural area (check eligibility at usda.gov). Income limits apply — household income must be below 115% of the area median income for your county. Primary residence only. Decent credit (typically 640+ for automated approval; lower scores may be manually reviewed). U.S. citizenship or qualified alien status. Florida eligible areas: Many smaller towns and rural areas qualify. Surprising inclusions: parts of Pasco, Polk, Alachua, Columbia, and other counties have USDA-eligible zones. Check specific address eligibility at the USDA website. Not eligible: Tampa, Orlando, Miami core areas and their immediate suburbs. Annual guarantee fee: 0.35% of loan balance (much less than FHA MIP). One-time upfront guarantee fee: 1% of loan amount. Best for: buyers in qualifying areas who have limited down payment savings but stable income."
