    "What is a jumbo loan and when do I need one in Florida?",
    "A jumbo loan is any mortgage that exceeds the conforming loan limits set by Fannie Mae and Freddie Mac. For 2024, the standard conforming limit in most of Florida is $766,550. If you need a loan above this amount, you need a jumbo loan. Key characteristics of jumbo loans: Higher requirements: typically 700+ credit score, 10-20% down payment, extensive asset documentation. No PMI on most jumbo products — but lenders compensate with higher rates or structure requirements. Higher rates: typically 0.25-0.75% above conforming rates (this gap has been smaller or negative in recent years). Stricter DTI requirements: most jumbo lenders want back-end DTI under 43%. More documentation: 24 months of bank statements, business financials if self-employed. Where you need them in Florida: South Florida (Miami-Dade, Broward, Palm Beach) — most $700K+ purchases exceed conforming limits. Coastal areas throughout Florida. Any home in Tampa Bay priced above $766K. Portfolio lenders often have the best jumbo products — they hold the loans in-house rather than selling to Fannie/Freddie, giving them flexibility on terms. Shop multiple lenders for jumbo loans — rate differences of 0.5%+ on large loans have enormous dollar impact."
